        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 25 at 10:16PM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 1015 PM CDT, a strong thunderstorm was located 6 miles southeast
of Powers Lake, or 14 miles northwest of Stanley, moving east at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Powers Lake and Lostwood.
</description>
        <instruction>This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 200 AM CDT for
north central and northwestern North Dakota.</instruction>
